<subSubSection pageId="156" pageNumber="727" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="156.[715,1303,2402,2820]" pageId="156" pageNumber="727">
Until recently, 
<taxonomicName box="[928,1077,2473,2506]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Cephalophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="156" pageNumber="727" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="johnston">C. johnston</taxonomicName>
: was considered to be a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[1019,1139,2512,2545]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Cephalophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="156" pageNumber="727" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="weynsi">C. weynsi</taxonomicName>
. Johnston's Duiker may perhaps hybridize with 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Cephalophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="156" pageNumber="727" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="harvey">C. harvey</taxonomicName>
: in 
<collectingCountry box="[809,896,2594,2623]" name="Kenya" pageId="156" pageNumber="727">Kenya</collectingCountry>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
